Pregnant Woman Riding Pillion Dies After Traffic Cop Kicks Her Bike For Not Wearing Helmet
	 	 	 	 CONTENT 
Pregnant Woman Riding Pillion Dies After Traffic Cop Kicks Her Bike For Not Wearing Helmet

Pregnant Woman Riding Pillion Dies After Traffic Cop Kicks Her Bike For Not Wearing Helmet

Protests erupted in Tamil Nadu's Trichy on Wednesday evening after a woman was killed on the road after being chased by the cops. 30-year-old Usha was killed after a traffic inspector allegedly kicked the two-wheeler on which she was travelling with her husband at Thuvakudi near Trichy.

The incident happened when Usha's husband Raja who was riding the bike without wearing helmet tried to escape the traffic cops.

Even after the cops asked Raja to stop the two-wheeler, he ignored and moved on.

According to eyewitnesses, the move irritated a police officer, Kamaraj, chased them on another bike. He allegedly kicked the bike making it wobble and both the husband and wife fell on the ground.

Usha who was pregnant died on the spot, while Raja has suffered serious injuries from the fall. As people began gathering at the spot, the inspector fled the scene.

Relatives of the couple and locals who gathered at the spot blocked the roads for hours, bringing the traffic to a standstill.

After hours of protest, the inspector was arrested.

